pageContext.claim: “The protesters, who, the day before tried to burn down the church. You know, everyone was saying, 'Oh, they were so wonderful.' They weren't wonderful. They tried to burn down the church. And it was, they told me, the same group. A similar group.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence protestors tried to burn down the church. It was not a major fire. Only a small room in the basement of the church, a nursery, had been damaged and the main sanctuary was not harmed at all.
